By: Representative Corbett of the 174th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act providing a new charter for the City of Hoboken, Georgia, approved
2 March 24, 1976 (Ga. L. 1976, p. 3060), as amended, so as to revise the compensation of the
3 mayor and councilmembers; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and
4 for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 An Act providing a new charter for the City of Hoboken, Georgia, approved March 24, 1976
8 (Ga. L. 1976, p. 3060), as amended, is amended by revising Section 2.04 as follows:
9 "SECTION 2.04.
10 Compensation and expenses.
11 The mayor shall receive as compensation for his or her services $475.00 per month. Each
12 councilmember shall receive as compensation for his or her services $175.00 per month.
13 The mayor and councilmembers shall also be entitled to be reimbursed for their actual and
14 necessary expenses incurred in the performance of their duties."
